output: For each test case, print a message informing if the second number fit ("encaixa" in portughese) or didn't fit ("nao encaixa") in the first number.
input:
The input consists of several test cases. The first line of input contains an integer N that indicates 
	the number of test cases. Each test case consists of two numbers A and B greather than
	zero, with up to 1000 digits each.
name: Fit or Dont Fit II
description:
Paulinho have again in your hands another problem. Now the teacher asked him to make a new program 
	to verify from two big numbers A and B, if B corresponds to the last digit of A.
